"Clear brown pour with lasting, clingy off-white foam - looks great! Aroma of some esters and malt, with some floral notes, but not much hop in the nose. Taste is biscuit and malty. Pretty good, but not on the level of Dogfish IBA."
""
"A decent enough brown ale. A ""hoppy brown ale"" as the bottle says, pretty balanced and drinkable. Serve at 50 degrees."
"12 ounce bottle into pint glass, bottled on 11/13/2014. Pours slightly hazy light reddish brown color with a 1-2 finger dense and rocky light khaki head with great retention, that reduces to a small cap that lingers. Nice spotty soapy lacing clings on the glass, with a fair amount of streaming carbonation. Aromas of caramel, toast, brown sugar, brown bread, light chocolate, light nuttiness, light citrus/pine, herbal, grass, and herbal/toasted earthiness. Nice and pleasant aromas with good balance and complexity of dark/bready malt and earthy hop notes; with solid strength. Taste of caramel, toast, brown sugar, brown bread, nuttiness, light chocolate, pine, herbal, grass, light citrus, and herbal/toasted earthiness. Good amount of herbal/pine bitterness on the finish; with lingering notes of caramel, toast, brown sugar, brown bread, nuttiness, light chocolate, pine, and herbal/toasted earthiness on the finish for a good bit. Nice balance, robustness, and complexity of dark/bready malt and earthy hop flavors; with a good malt/bitterness balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Medium carbonation and body; with a smooth, moderately sticky, and lightly creamy/bready mouthfeel that is nice. Alcohol is well hidden with minimal warming present after the finish. Overall this is a nice hoppy brown ale. All around good complexity, robustness, and balance of dark/bready malt and earthy hop flavors; and very smooth and fairly crisp to drink. A nicely enjoyable offering."
