"The puns...why can't they be any good?  Anyway, this stuff pours a clear garnet-sienna topped by a finger of glowing dirty cream foam.  The nose comprises dry maple syrup, mild caramel, mixed greens, a hint of pine, and a twinge of vague nuttiness.  The taste leads with some meek caramel and biscuit, then goes into a wave of greens, grass, and mild pine, and then ends with a soft touch of walnut.  The body is a light medium, with a light moderate carbonation and a fluid feel.  Overall, this one didn't quite do it for me.  The greens overpower most of the malts, and those greens don't have that much character in and of themselves.  Pass."
"a very nice product.  A good brown ale, with a nice balance of malts and a bit of hop bite.    I do not like MAgic Hat # 9, but this, and their ""Heart of Darkness"" are fine products (much above average)."
