"Clear mahogany brown. Light khaki head. Creamy, but short lived. Better than average lacing. Aroma is nutty/chocolatey with grassy hops - not particularly bright, just average 'brown ale'. Caramelish, nutty, and lightly milk-chocolate in the flavor. Herbal, floral and subtly piney hops 'spruce it up' a bit. Solidly bitter. Dry finish. Remains an average 'brown ale' with a few extra hops thrown in, but balanced and drinkable."
