"im glad hoppy brown ales are making a comeback, they are the perfect fall beer, and this one tastes pretty good. its a little generic on the hop front, but the balance between the chocolate malt and the bittering is well done, and there is a definite warming quality to a couple of these. one thing I might change is the body, its real thin I think for the season and the style, and even light for the bold flavor profile of the beer. its also a bit under carbonated, which never happens with magic hat but is not nice in this particular beer. a get a neat toasted coconut flavor to the grain, and then the hops, it almost has a tropical element to it that way. this is a style I want to see more of, but a beer that's unique but far from perfect. a few tweaks for next year and this one will be money. I think the abv is right on too for the style and the season."
